casebody.data:
Rosalyn HARRIS-OFFUT
v.
THE NORTH CAROLINA BOARD OF LICENSED PROFESSIONAL COUNSELORS. No. 3P06. Supreme Court of North Carolina. June 29, 2006. King V. Cheek, Jr., Romallus O. Murphy, Greensboro, for Harris-Offutt. William H. Borden, Special Deputy Attorney General, for Board of LPC.

ORDER

Upon consideration of the conditional petition filed on the 12th day of January 2006 by Defendant in this matter for discretionary review of the decision of the North Carolina Court of Appeals pursuant to G.S. 7A-31, the following order was entered and is hereby certified to the North Carolina Court of Appeals:

"Dismissed as moot by order of the Court in conference, this the 29th day of June 2006."
